<entry id="nazareno" guid="c81cb01e-001f-50d8-9a94-841ae52667d2"><lexical-unit><form lang="tl"><text>nazareno</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="nazareno_0" guid="a88bd51b-579f-53a6-b445-763a6abad43f"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Nazarene</text></gloss></sense><sense id="nazareno_1" guid="60508442-919f-52d0-8e8b-9d03f2c24b8f"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Nazarene; Jesus Christ</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="nazaret" guid="1d4ad7d3-ac6a-522e-94ef-ac75a565edf3"><lexical-unit><form lang="tl"><text>nazaret</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="nazaret_0" guid="1afb3d3b-7ad4-57bb-8d89-aec9c0eb7565"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Nazareth (a city in northern Israel)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="negosyo" guid="18b6aaa6-8434-5522-85da-25f207d1695a"><lexical-unit><form lang="tl"><text>negosyo</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="negosyo_0" guid="a9f0a554-395d-50fb-b85a-aac52f8cb3cb"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>business</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="ng" guid="1df19758-5ad3-56ce-86c6-b991fdff5fa2"><lexical-unit><form lang="tl"><text>ng</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="ng_0" guid="32afa921-6963-5c4d-95bb-b84db2c97339"><grammatical-info value="Adposition"/><gloss lang="en"><text>marks the core participant/s within a clause that is not otherwise focused using the case marker "ang", i.e.:</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ng_1" guid="b6ba0fce-c94a-51dc-a339-2db7cbb8d4ed"><grammatical-info value="Adposition"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the patient, undergoer, or theme of the action in actor-trigger verbs</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ng_2" guid="579d269b-1264-55c9-a30c-e1cf69b9654e"><grammatical-info value="Adposition"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the agent, doer, or experiencer of the action in patient-trigger verbs</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ng_3" guid="be1e3a96-f33a-58d6-a626-ebae7a87863b"><grammatical-info value="Adposition"/><gloss lang="en"><text>both the agent and patient of the action in oblique-trigger constructions</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ng_4" guid="53b6dd9b-7ed5-5770-86d7-2468d461c723"><grammatical-info value="Adposition"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the location or direction treated as the object-like complement of the motion: to, into, towards; from, off of</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ng_5" guid="a281949a-fda5-560f-912f-9dd6679e161c"><grammatical-info value="Adposition"/><gloss lang="en"><text>marks possession: of, 's</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ng_6" guid="bc919680-8bff-5581-8d30-68f5ab1136a2"><grammatical-info value="Adposition"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the sixteenth letter of the Filipino alphabet, called en dyi and written in the Latin script</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ng_7" guid="786369c2-fca0-5c8f-a420-e94c948a4b68"><grammatical-info value="Adposition"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the twelfth letter of the Abakada alphabet, called nga and written in the Latin script</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="nga" guid="a081b7c3-92bc-5459-9e32-b4fffbc881de"><lexical-unit><form lang="tl"><text>nga</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="nga_0" guid="251b7a0c-a6ba-5765-af68-b2e4790754da"><grammatical-info value="Adverb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the name of the Latin script letter Ng/ng, in the Abakada alphabet</text></gloss></sense><sense id="nga_1" guid="496019e2-90dd-543a-a4b9-c9baeed01592"><grammatical-info value="Adverb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Used to emphasize affirmation, confirmation, or something being true: indeed; really; certainly</text></gloss></sense><sense id="nga_2" guid="77d80c69-4735-5b12-b7ed-4cc54962adfc"><grammatical-info value="Adverb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Used to give a polite request: kindly; please</text></gloss></sense><sense id="nga_3" guid="5071925c-3901-586f-a220-2ec0ac1ab48e"><grammatical-info value="Adverb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Used to express strong encouragement</text></gloss></sense><sense id="nga_4" guid="1db92ca3-3629-541f-9974-918e066a8cc8"><grammatical-info value="Adverb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Used to express a wish of moderate force</text></gloss></sense></entry>
