<entry id="santo" guid="bc2d0f2a-c37f-57e3-a5ba-95020a00eb0b"><lexical-unit><form lang="tl"><text>santo</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="santo_0" guid="af87e707-2952-5bb6-ab03-1f5eff0b96ef"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>saint (especially a male saint)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="santo_1" guid="303e3846-7893-5925-aa8b-4b6fae982593"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>image or statue of a saint</text></gloss></sense><sense id="santo_2" guid="5628fa83-88bf-57d4-ad87-48a7f22029ed"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>referring to an important figure, item, or event which had a masculine gender in Spanish: holy; sacred (used in certain expressions)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="santo_3" guid="9752d4e4-c32d-59f7-a78c-4022ed5d4786"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>title used with the name of the male saints Tomas, Tome, Domingo, and Toribio: Saint; St.</text></gloss></sense><sense id="santo_4" guid="c4601a2c-bae0-54bd-ac0f-4ed6489f5d8e"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>alternative letter-case form of santo when referring to an important figure, item, or event which had a masculine gender in Spanish: Holy</text></gloss></sense></entry>
